text: I don't want to call it a 'bright side,' but will the soaring number of #COVID19 cases in many US states make it easier to detect an efficacy signal in Phase 3 trials of #vaccines?

The power of statistics: in US, Blacks' mortality from #COVID19 >> whites'. Regression analysis ruled out income, poverty, obesity, diabetes as explanations. Which leaves us with  . . . .: https://t.co/peip7cJhN0

For 6 months there's been skepticism about 'asymptomatic' #COVID19 , with doubters saying nah, they're just pre-symptomatic. Study of #DiamondPrincess passengers lays that to rest: https://t.co/mexsgoSpkL

Read how @raceandhealth is stepping up during pandemic to tackle racism in healthcare & health disparities: https://t.co/JEWbWFPI4W. Key quote in @scchak story: Saying  more Black & brown people are likely to die from Covid-19 b/c they have high b.p. "is lazy thinking."

So many #COVID19 models, but with many now projecting to Oct. 1 here's one that's been on the money for months: https://t.co/Lyodl7UPhp.  Preview (1st column is now, 2nd is 10/1): https://t.co/qwmDc8s5Xy
It's the masks: 78k fewer #COVID19 infections in Italy, 66k fewer in #NYC due to masking alone. Note the senior author on this one, who knows a bit about airborne particles: https://t.co/9ARlc1zEIs.
After quite the FU, #WHO 'clarifies' comments on asymptomatic spread of #COVID19. ‘We don’t actually have that answer yet,’ @DrewQJoseph reports https://t.co/IRLjnZMYE0 via @statnews

2/2 WHO’s comment was based on “evidence from member states” (not yet shared). "Communicating preliminary data" on Covid-19 "can have tremendous negative impact on how the public and policy makers respond to the pandemic." Calls on WHO to release data, brief media & public.

1/n After #WHO minimizes role of people w/o symptoms in spreading #COVID19 , WTF??!! reaction grows. From @HarvardGH: "The best evidence suggests that people w/o symptoms can and do readily spread SARS-CoV2.... may be most infectious in the days before they become symptomatic"

NPIs vs. #Covid_19 averted 3.1M deaths in Europe, drove R to < 1. But which NPI? If we need 60% drop in contacts, do some NPIs (incl'g #facemasks) get us 1/2way there while others add just a few % points? Really need to figure this out before next wave:  https://t.co/vf9A3uHiUZ
